    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Key Takeaway }</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        Combined operations on decimals involve performing multiple arithmetic 
        operations such as addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division within a single expression. 
        We follow the order of brackets, division, multiplication, addition, and 
        finally Subtraction (BODMAS) when working out multiple operations.
    </p>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Work out each of the following:
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="a)" cols="2">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>4.85 - 56.45 + 89.75</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>2.5 \times 5.1 \div 1.7 - 3.9 + 7.5</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <ol marker="a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>4.85 - 56.45 + 89.75</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            We first perform addition, then subtraction.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            We rearrange the operation as <m>4.85 + 89.75 - 56.45 </m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            To add decimal numbers, align them vertically.
                        </p>
                        <tabular>
                            <row>
                                <cell halign="right"><m>4.85</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row bottom="major">
                                <cell><m>+\,89.75</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row bottom="major">
                                <cell halign="right"><m>94.60</m></cell>
                            </row>
                        </tabular>
                        <p>
                            Then, we perform the subtraction. <m>94.60 - 56.45</m>
                        </p>
                        <tabular>
                            <row>
                                <cell halign="right"><m>94.60</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row bottom="major">
                                <cell><m>-\,56.45</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row bottom="major">
                                <cell halign="right"><m>38.15</m></cell>
                            </row>
                        </tabular>
                        <p>
                            Thus, <m>4.85 - 56.45 + 89.75 = 38.15</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Given the expression:
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <me>2.5 \times 5.1 \div 1.7 - 3.9 + 6.5</me>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Perform the division first.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <me>
                                5.1 \div 1.7
                            </me>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Express the decimals as fractions and then we multiply the dividend by the reciprocal of the divisor:
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>\frac{51}{10} \div \frac{17}{10}= \frac{51}{10} \times \frac{10}{17} = \frac{51 \times 10}{10 \times 17} = \frac{510}{170} = 3</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Now, the expression simplifies to:
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <me>
                                2.5 \times 3 - 3.9 + 6.5
                            </me>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Perform the multiplication:
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <me>
                                2.5 \times 3 = \frac{25}{10} \times 3 = \frac{25 \times 3}{10} = \frac{75}{10} = 7.5
                            </me>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Now, the expression reduces to: 
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <me>7.5 - 3.9 + 6.5</me>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Perform the addition: 
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <me>7.5 + 6.5 = 14</me>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            subtract <m>3.9</m> from <m>14.</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>14 - 3.9 = 10.1 </m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
